  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 7
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Raft Internals\n\nThis dashboard exposes the low-level mechanics of the **Raft consensus algorithm** as implemented by the Hazelcast CP Subsystem.\nUse it to diagnose replication problems, log pressure, and leadership instability.\n\n**Key questions this dashboard answers:**\n- Is the Raft log being committed and applied at the same pace on all members? *(Commit Index vs Last Applied)*\n- How close is the log to being full \u2014 i.e., will new writes be rejected soon? *(Available Log Capacity)*\n- How often are leader elections happening, and are they getting more frequent? *(Elections / Term)*\n- Which member is the current leader of each CP group, and when did that last change? *(Leader Timeline)*\n\n**Filters:** use **CP Group** to isolate a single group. Use **Member** to compare behaviour across specific nodes.\n\n**Normal state:** commit lag near 0, term flat, available capacity > 3 000, one stable leader per group.\n**Warning signs:** commit lag growing, term stepping up repeatedly, capacity below 1 000, or leadership bouncing between members."
      },
      "transparent": true
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Log Replication",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "h": 1
      },
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Commit Index vs Last Applied",
      "description": "commitIndex leads lastApplied. A persistent gap means followers are not applying entries as fast as the leader commits them.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "prometheus"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 8,
        "w": 12,
        "h": 8
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus"
          },
          "expr": "max by (name) (hz_raft_group_commitIndex{mc_cluster=\"$cluster\", name=~\"$cp_group\"})",
          "legendFormat": "commitIndex \u2013 {{name}}",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "prometheus"
          },
          "expr": "max by (name) (hz_raft_group_lastApplied{mc_cluster=\"$cluster\", name=~\"$cp_group\"})",
          "legendFormat": "lastApplied \u2013 {{name}}",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "options": {
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi"
        },
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "bottom",
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull",
            "max"
          ]
        }
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 6
          },
          "min": 0,
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Commit Rate (entries/s)",
      "description": "Rate at which new log entries are being committed per group. Drops to 0 under no write load.",
